reviews.text: Very good meal and super fair price. Thank you.

The quality of the steak disappointing me (very chewy).may be i should order lamb rack as recommended.in fact the price is cheap for such a set dinner.the salad is good.soup is tiny.if i chose lamb may be I'll make a four star.after all, the whole set is value for money.

My first review and will be completely honest. Horrible service- the server had a very bad attitude- he ignored us when we enthusiastically asked for recommendations, argued with us when we told him he gave us extra soup but then rudely tried to get it back (which we obviously refused). I saw him get out food and linger behind the counter (he rearranged leaflets on a desk before serving...why?? so our food will get cold to piss us off?) We asked for his attention but he blatantly ignored until we called him loudly and everyone's attention was on him. Refused to give us packing materials when asked but really? I understand if a buffet doesnt allow... The pasta was mediocre, but the lamb and sirloin was good.

Overall the service was just unncessarily stressful, and it's the first horrible one I had in Jordan or anywhere. Ofher restaurants nearby had wonderful or just normal decent services. I will never go back to mileson and I do not recommend this agonizing experience to anyone.
Nice services and super delicious food with reasonable price
